KZN Transport, Community Safety and Liaison MEC Bheki Ntuli @KZNTransport DURBAN - KwaZulu-Natal MEC for Transport, Community Safety and Liaison, Bheki Ntuli, has died aged 63. The ANC in the province confirmed Ntuli's death in a media statement on Saturday. He was also ANC Provincial Executive Committee (PEC) member. ANC KwaZulu-Natal spokesperson, Nhlakanipho Ntombela, said Ntuli died after "a short illness". Ntombela said the party will release an official statement once the Office of the Premier has made anÂ announcement. The ANC called for space for the Ntuli family to mourn until further details are announced.